{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857434220,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d7959fa01001BiedfiTbObLuBw","messageID":"msg_d7959f36c001cCgp4Wk1lNbIbJ","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3601242cec0a43359ba11332","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-023/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-023/design.md`, `changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** AR-022 (publish command) — requires published agent endpoint\n9: \n10: ## T1. 实现 InvokeRuntime 类\n11: \n12: - [ ] 1.1 创建 `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n13: - [ ] 1.2 定义 `InvokeRuntime` 类：`__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n14: - [ ] 1.3 实现 `invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`：\n15:   - 加载 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n16:   - 校验 `agent_endpoint` 存在 → 否则 `ValueError`\n17:   - 发送 HTTP POST 请求到 endpoint\n18:   - 返回响应结果\n19: - [ ] 1.4 创建对应测试文件\n20: \n21: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py -v` 全部通过\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## T2. 增强 StatusRuntime 类\n26: \n27: - [ ] 2.1 修改 `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n28: - [ ] 2.2 实现 `status(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`：\n29:   - 加载 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n30:   - 根据 `k8s_deployment.type` 路由到正确的状态查询\n31:   - 返回状态信息\n32: - [ ] 2.3 实现/增强 `_get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n33: - [ ] 2.4 创建对应测试文件\n34: \n35: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py -v` 全部通过\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## T3. 实现 CLI invoke 命令入口\n40: \n41: - [ ] 3.1 在 `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` 中添加 `invoke` 命令\n42: - [ ] 3.2 选项：`workspace`, `prompt`, `verbose`\n43: - [ ] 3.3 命令体：调用 `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`，Rich 格式输出响应\n44: - [ ] 3.4 创建对应测试文件\n45: \n46: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py -v` 全部通过\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## T4. 实现 CLI status 命令入口\n51: \n52: - [ ] 4.1 在 `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` 中添加 `status` 命令\n53: - [ ] 4.2 选项：`workspace`, `verbose`\n54: - [ ] 4.3 命令体：调用 `StatusRuntime.status()`，Rich Table 格式输出状态\n55: - [ ] 4.4 创建对应测试文件\n56: \n57: **Verification:** `pytest cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_status_command.py -v` 全部通过\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## T5. 代码质量门禁与最终验证\n62: \n63: - [ ] 5.1 运行 `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/` 确认无 lint 错误\n64: - [ ] 5.2 运行 `ruff format --check cmd/cli/agentcube/` 确认格式合规\n65: - [ ] 5.3 运行 `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` 确认无类型错误\n66: - [ ] 5.4 运行 `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v --cov=agentcube` 确认覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n67: - [ ] 5.5 运行 `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` 确认帮助输出\n68: - [ ] 5.6 运行 `kubectl-agentcube status --help` 确认帮助输出\n69: \n70: **Verification:** 以上全部通过；exit code 均为 0\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## Task Dependencies\n75: \n76: ```\n77: T1 (InvokeRuntime) ───────────────────────────────┐\n78:                                                    │\n79: T2 (StatusRuntime) ────────────────────────────────┤\n80:                                                    │\n81: T3 (CLI invoke 命令) ←── T1 ───────────────────────┤\n82:                                                    │\n83: T4 (CLI status 命令) ←── T2 ───────────────────────┤\n84:                                                    │\n85: T5 (质量门禁) ←── T3, T4 ──────────────────────────┘\n86: ```\n87: \n88: **Parallel execution:**\n89: - T1 和 T2 可并行开发\n90: - T3 需 T1 完成后开始\n91: - T4 需 T2 完成后开始\n92: - T3 和 T4 可并行开发\n93: - T5 需所有前置任务完成\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Acceptance Criteria\n98: \n99: | # | Criterion | Command |\n100: |---|-----------|---------|\n101: | AC1 | invoke 命令接受 workspace 和 prompt 选项 | `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` |\n102: | AC2 | status 命令接受 workspace 选项 | `kubectl-agentcube status --help` |\n103: | AC3 | 未发布的 agent invoke 报错 | 无 `agent_endpoint` → `ValueError` |\n104: | AC4 | invoke 发送 HTTP 请求并显示响应 | Rich 格式输出 |\n105: | AC5 | status 查询并显示部署状态 | Rich Table 格式 |\n106: | AC6 | 覆盖率 ≥ 80% | `pytest --cov=agentcube` |\n107: | AC7 | ruff lint 无错误 | `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n108: | AC8 | mypy 类型检查无错误 | `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` |\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-023/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-023/design.md`, `changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** AR-022 (publish command) — requires published agent endpoint\n\n## T1. 实现 InvokeRuntime 类\n\n- [ ] 1.1 创建 `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n- [ ] 1.2 定义 `InvokeRuntime` 类：`__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n- [ ] 1.3 实现 `invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`：\n  - 加载 `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - 校验 `agent_endpoint` 存在 → 否则 `ValueError`\n  - 发送 HTTP POST 请求到 endpoint\n  - 返回响应结果\n- [ ] 1.4 创建对应测试文件\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775857434205,"end":1775857434218}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857435521,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d7959fedd001OMiMG3d2qey35W","messageID":"msg_d7959f36c001cCgp4Wk1lNbIbJ","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_43d3e360570247e7b07230f3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: `invoke` command\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that sends an HTTP request to a deployed agent endpoint.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Command signature\n17: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed\n18: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke --help`\n19: - **THEN** it SHALL show options for workspace, input/prompt, and verbose\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Invoke with endpoint from metadata\n22: - **GIVEN** the workspace has been published and `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `agent_endpoint`\n23: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke -f <workspace> --prompt \"hello\"`\n24: - **THEN** the system SHALL send an HTTP POST request to the endpoint and display the response\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Invoke without published endpoint\n27: - **GIVEN** the workspace has not been published or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n28: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke`\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the agent has not been published\n30: \n31: ### Requirement: `status` command\n32: \n33: The system SHALL provide a `status` subcommand that queries the deployment status of an agent.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Command signature\n36: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed\n37: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube status --help`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL show options for workspace and verbose\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Status from AgentRuntime CR\n41: - **GIVEN** the agent was published with `provider=agentcube`\n42: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube status -f <workspace>`\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL query the AgentRuntime CR status and display it\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Status from K8s Deployment\n46: - **GIVEN** the agent was published with `provider=k8s`\n47: - **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube status -f <workspace>`\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL query the Deployment status and display it\n49: \n50: ## File changes\n51: \n52: | Action | File | Description |\n53: |--------|------|-------------|\n54: | Modify | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `invoke` and `status` Typer commands |\n55: | Add | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | InvokeRuntime class |\n56: | Modify | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Enhance StatusRuntime class |\n57: | Add | `tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py` | CLI invoke command tests |\n58: | Add | `tests/cli/test_status_command.py` | CLI status command tests |\n59: | Add | `tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py` | InvokeRuntime unit tests |\n60: | Add | `tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py` | StatusRuntime unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 60 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `invoke` command\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that sends an HTTP request to a deployed agent endpoint.\n\n#### Scenario: Command signature\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke --help`\n- **THEN** it SHALL show options for workspace, input/prompt, and verbose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857435512,"end":1775857435519}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857436749,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d795a040d001K1tgFNLY4B96E3","messageID":"msg_d7959f36c001cCgp4Wk1lNbIbJ","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2264f0d6091e47fdaf132fa6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n4: **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n9: \n10: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n11: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n12: - [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n13: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n14: \n15: ## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n16: \n17: - [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n18: - [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n19: - [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n20: - [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple\n21: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_id` raises `ValueError`\n22: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_endpoint` raises `ValueError`\n23: \n24: ## T-3: InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation\n25: \n26: - [ ] Implement `_direct_http_invocation(endpoint: str, payload: Dict, headers: Dict[str, str], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict`\n27: - [ ] POST JSON to `{endpoint}` using `httpx` (sync client)\n28: - [ ] Parse JSON response; return parsed dict\n29: - [ ] On non-2xx status, raise exception with status code and response body\n30: - [ ] Write test: successful POST returns parsed JSON response\n31: - [ ] Write test: non-2xx response raises exception with status code\n32: - [ ] Write test: custom headers are included in request\n33: \n34: ## T-4: InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n35: \n36: - [ ] Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path) -> Dict`\n37: - [ ] Load metadata; if `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n38: - [ ] If `metadata.session_id` exists, inject header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id`\n39: - [ ] POST JSON to rewritten endpoint; return parsed response\n40: - [ ] Write test: endpoint rewriting when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n41: - [ ] Write test: session header injection when `session_id` present\n42: - [ ] Write test: no rewriting when deployment type is not `AgentRuntime`\n43: - [ ] Write test: no session header when `session_id` is absent\n44: \n45: ## T-5: InvokeRuntime.invoke (orchestration)\n46: \n47: - [ ] Implement `invoke(workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict, headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict`\n48: - [ ] Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` → get metadata, agent_id, endpoint\n49: - [ ] If `self.provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n50: - [ ] Otherwise, call `_direct_http_invocation`\n51: - [ ] Return the response\n52: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n53: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_direct_http_invocation`\n54: \n55: ## T-6: invoke CLI command entry point\n56: \n57: - [ ] Add `invoke()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n58: - [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `payload` (`--payload`, default `\"{}\"`), `header_list` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n59: - [ ] Parse `--payload` as JSON; on invalid JSON, print `Error: Invalid JSON payload: {detail}` in red, exit code `1`\n60: - [ ] Parse `--header` entries: split on first `:`, strip key/value; on missing `:`, print `Error: Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'.` in red, exit code `1`\n61: - [ ] Merge multiple headers into single `Dict[str, str]`\n62: - [ ] Call `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` within error handler\n63: - [ ] On success, print response (Rich-formatted if JSON, raw text otherwise)\n64: - [ ] On error, use `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n65: - [ ] Write test: successful invoke prints response, exit 0\n66: - [ ] Write test: invalid JSON payload → error message, exit 1\n67: - [ ] Write test: invalid header format → error message, exit 1\n68: - [ ] Write test: multiple headers merged correctly\n69: - [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n70: - [ ] Write test: quiet error prints message only, exit 1\n71: \n72: ## T-7: StatusRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n73: \n74: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class\n75: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n76: - [ ] Add `StatusRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n77: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly\n78: \n79: ## T-8: StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status\n80: \n81: - [ ] Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n82: - [ ] Use `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(name)` to fetch CR\n83: - [ ] If CR exists and has `status` field → return `{\"status\": cr_status, \"endpoint\": cr_agentEndpoint, ...}`\n84: - [ ] If CR exists but no `status` field → return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}`\n85: - [ ] If CR not found → return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}`\n86: - [ ] Write test: CR exists with status → returns status + endpoint\n87: - [ ] Write test: CR exists without status → returns `created_no_status`\n88: - [ ] Write test: CR not found → returns `not_found_in_k8s`\n89: \n90: ## T-9: StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status\n91: \n92: - [ ] Implement `_get_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n93: - [ ] Call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)` (see T-11)\n94: - [ ] Return the result dict\n95: - [ ] Write test: calls `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and returns result\n96: \n97: ## T-10: StatusRuntime.get_status (orchestration)\n98: \n99: - [ ] Implement `get_status(workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict`\n100: - [ ] Load metadata from workspace via `MetadataService`\n101: - [ ] If no `agent_id` → return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n102: - [ ] If `provider == \"agentcube\"` (or default), call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n103: - [ ] Otherwise, call `_get_k8s_status`\n104: - [ ] Return the status dict\n105: - [ ] Write test: no `agent_id` → returns `not_published`\n106: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n107: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_get_k8s_status`\n108: \n109: ## T-11: KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status\n110: \n111: - [ ] Add `get_agent_status(agent_name: str) -> Dict` to `KubernetesProvider`\n112: - [ ] Query deployment status via `AppsV1Api.read_namespaced_deployment_status`\n113: - [ ] Query pod status via `CoreV1Api.list_namespaced_pod` with label selector\n114: - [ ] Return dict with deployment status, pod statuses, endpoint info\n115: - [ ] On 404, return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n116: - [ ] Write test: deployment found with ready pods → returns status\n117: - [ ] Write test: deployment not found → returns `not_found`\n118: \n119: ## T-12: status CLI command entry point\n120: \n121: - [ ] Add `status()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n122: - [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n123: - [ ] Call `StatusRuntime.get_status()`\n124: - [ ] If status == `\"not_published\"` → print guidance to run `publish` first, exit code `1`\n125: - [ ] If status == `\"error\"` → print error details, exit code `1`\n126: - [ ] Otherwise, render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value (at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider)\n127: - [ ] On exception, use `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n128: - [ ] Write test: not_published → guidance message, exit 1\n129: - [ ] Write test: error status → error details, exit 1\n130: - [ ] Write test: valid status → Rich Table rendered with required fields\n131: - [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n132: \n133: ## T-13: Provider validation (cross-cutting)\n134: \n135: - [ ] Add provider validation to both `invoke` and `status` commands: reject values other than `\"agentcube\"` / `\"k8s\"`\n136: - [ ] Write test: invalid provider → error message, exit 1\n137: \n138: ## T-14: Integration tests\n139: \n140: - [ ] Write integration test: full invoke flow with mocked HTTP (mock `httpx.Client`)\n141: - [ ] Write integration test: full status flow with mocked K8s (mock `AgentCubeProvider` / `KubernetesProvider`)\n142: - [ ] Write integration test: invoke with session header end-to-end (mocked)\n143: \n144: ## T-15: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n145: \n146: - [ ] `ruff check agentcube/` — no violations\n147: - [ ] `mypy agentcube/` — no type errors\n148: - [ ] `pytest tests/ -v` — all pass\n149: - [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 80%\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Dependency Graph\n154: \n155: ```\n156: T-1  ──┬── T-2 ──┬── T-5 ── T-6\n157:        │          │\n158:        │          └── T-4 ──┘\n159:        │\n160:        └── T-3 ──┘\n161: \n162: T-7  ──┬── T-8 ──┬── T-10 ── T-12\n163:        │          │\n164:        └── T-9 ──┘  (T-9 depends on T-11)\n165: \n166: T-11 ── T-9\n167: \n168: T-13 ── (T-6, T-12)\n169: \n170: T-14 ── (T-6, T-12)\n171: \n172: T-15 ── (all above)\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ## Parallelizable Groups\n176: \n177: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n178: |-------|-------|---------------|\n179: | G1 | T-1, T-7 | None |\n180: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-11 | T-1 |\n181: | G3 | T-4, T-8, T-9 | T-2, T-11 |\n182: | G4 | T-5, T-10 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-8, T-9 |\n183: | G5 | T-6, T-12, T-13 | T-5, T-10 |\n184: | G6 | T-14 | T-6, T-12 |\n185: | G7 | T-15 | All above |\n\n(End of file - total 185 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n- [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n- [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n\n## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n\n- [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n- [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n- [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n- [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775857436737,"end":1775857436746}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775857436780,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d795a084d001rtICTl08CrW2bf","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7959f36c001cCgp4Wk1lNbIbJ","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":18505,"input":18271,"output":220,"reasoning":14,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.00542913}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775857438109,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d795a0d9a001oAm5VOyc8cyy4Y","messageID":"msg_d795a088c001UVQl0NKNwxzW4A","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857439938,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d795a103d001Che9B2TjQ3pc23","messageID":"msg_d795a088c001UVQl0NKNwxzW4A","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1d4c177edfbb4c9da41d6b15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"InvokeRuntime for invoking deployed agents via HTTP.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: import asyncio\n6: import json\n7: from pathlib import Path\n8: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n9: \n10: import httpx\n11: \n12: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n13: \n14: \n15: class InvokeRuntime:\n16:     \"\"\"Runtime for invoking deployed agents with provider-aware logic.\"\"\"\n17: \n18:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n19:         self.verbose = verbose\n20:         self.provider = provider\n21: \n22:     def invoke(\n23:         self,\n24:         workspace_path: Path,\n25:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n26:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n27:     ) -> Any:\n28:         \"\"\"Invoke a deployed agent with the given payload.\n29: \n30:         Args:\n31:             workspace_path: Path to the agent workspace.\n32:             payload: JSON payload to send to the agent.\n33:             headers: Optional HTTP headers to include.\n34: \n35:         Returns:\n36:             The response from the agent endpoint.\n37:         \"\"\"\n38:         metadata, agent_id, endpoint = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n39: \n40:         if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n41:             return asyncio.run(\n42:                 self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n43:                     agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path,\n44:                 )\n45:             )\n46:         else:\n47:             return asyncio.run(\n48:                 self._direct_http_invocation(\n49:                     endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path,\n50:                 )\n51:             )\n52: \n53:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n54:         self, workspace_path: Path,\n55:     ) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n56:         \"\"\"Validate that the workspace has published metadata.\n57: \n58:         Args:\n59:             workspace_path: Path to the agent workspace.\n60: \n61:         Returns:\n62:             Tuple of (metadata, agent_id, endpoint).\n63: \n64:         Raises:\n65:             ValueError: If the agent has not been published or endpoint is missing.\n66:         \"\"\"\n67:         service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n68:         metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n69: \n70:         if metadata is None:\n71:             raise ValueError(\n72:                 \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\"\n73:             )\n74: \n75:         if not metadata.agent_id:\n76:             raise ValueError(\n77:                 \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\"\n78:             )\n79:         if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n80:             raise ValueError(\n81:                 \"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\"\n82:             )\n83: \n84:         return metadata, metadata.agent_id, metadata.agent_endpoint\n85: \n86:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n87:         self,\n88:         agent_id: str,\n89:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n90:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n91:         endpoint: str,\n92:         workspace_path: Path,\n93:     ) -> Any:\n94:         \"\"\"Invoke via AgentCube AgentRuntime CR endpoint.\n95: \n96:         Rewrites the endpoint URL if k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\".\n97:         Adds X-Agentcube-Session-Id header if session_id exists in metadata.\n98: \n99:         Args:\n100:             agent_id: The agent ID.\n101:             payload: JSON payload to send.\n102:             headers: Optional HTTP headers.\n103:             endpoint: The base endpoint URL.\n104:             workspace_path: Path to the workspace (for loading metadata).\n105: \n106:         Returns:\n107:             Parsed JSON response.\n108:         \"\"\"\n109:         metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n110: \n111:         if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n112:             namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n113:             agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\n114:             base = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n115:             endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n116: \n117:         request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n118:         if metadata and metadata.session_id:\n119:             request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n120: \n121:         async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n122:             response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n123:             response.raise_for_status()\n124:             return response.json()\n125: \n126:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n127:         self,\n128:         endpoint: str,\n129:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n130:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n131:         workspace_path: Path,\n132:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n133:         \"\"\"Direct HTTP POST to the agent endpoint.\n134: \n135:         Args:\n136:             endpoint: The agent endpoint URL.\n137:             payload: JSON payload to send.\n138:             headers: Optional HTTP headers.\n139:             workspace_path: Path to the workspace (for loading metadata).\n140: \n141:         Returns:\n142:             Parsed JSON response.\n143:         \"\"\"\n144:         metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n145: \n146:         request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n147:         if metadata and metadata.session_id:\n148:             request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n149: \n150:         async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n151:             response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n152:             response.raise_for_status()\n153:             return response.json()\n\n(End of file - total 153 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"InvokeRuntime for invoking deployed agents via HTTP.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport asyncio\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n\nimport httpx\n\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n\n\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Runtime for invoking deployed agents with provider-aware logic.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py","time":{"start":1775857439929,"end":1775857439936}}}}
