{"type":"text","timestamp":1775857479565,"sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","part":{"id":"prt_d795a812400161vJjpJ5BX3bTu","messageID":"msg_d795a771a001G4BfwZrohzo8i5","sessionID":"ses_286a623ebffexQ6eQhlYTCp58v","type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis of the codebase, here's the summary:\n\n## AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Archive Summary\n\n### Completed\n\n**InvokeRuntime** (`invoke_runtime.py`):\n- Constructor with `verbose` and `provider` params\n- `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()` — loads metadata, validates `agent_id` and `agent_endpoint`\n- `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` — async HTTP POST with URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR, session header injection\n- `_direct_http_invocation()` — async HTTP POST for standard K8s endpoints\n- `invoke()` — orchestration routing by provider\n\n**StatusRuntime** (`status_runtime.py`):\n- Constructor with `verbose` and `provider` params\n- `_get_cr_k8s_status()` — queries AgentRuntime CR via `AgentCubeProvider`\n- `_get_k8s_status()` — delegates to `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n- `get_status()` — orchestration routing by provider, returns `not_published` if no `agent_id`\n\n**KubernetesProvider** extension:\n- `get_agent_status()` — queries deployment status, handles 404 gracefully\n\n**CLI commands** (`cli/main.py`):\n- `invoke` command — JSON payload parsing, header parsing (`key:value`), provider selection, Rich output\n- `status` command — Rich Table rendering, `not_published` guidance, error handling\n- Both commands use `_handle_error()` for consistent error reporting\n\n**Tests**:\n- `test_invoke_runtime.py` — constructor, valid invoke (both providers), not published, missing endpoint, URL rewriting, session header, custom headers, HTTP error, validate prerequisites\n- `test_status_runtime.py` — constructor, not published, CR exists/no-status/not-found, K8s running/pending/not-found, provider selection/override\n- `test_invoke_command.py` — success (both providers), default/custom payload, invalid JSON, single/multiple headers, invalid header, verbose/quiet errors, help\n- `test_status_command.py` — success (both providers), not published guidance, error status, verbose/quiet errors, help\n\n**Exports**: `runtime/__init__.py` updated with `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime`\n\n### Deferred / Known Issues\n\n1. **`UnboundLocalError` in `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`** — documented known bug where `response` is only assigned inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`. Out of scope for AR-023; CLI layer catches it via `_handle_error`.\n\n2. **Integration tests (T-14)** — no dedicated `test_invoke_status_integration.py` file found. Unit tests cover the flows with mocks, but no explicit end-to-end integration test file for session header flow or full mocked pipeline.\n\n3. **Provider validation in CLI (T-13)** — the `invoke` and `status` commands accept `--provider` but do not validate that it's one of `\"agentcube\"` or `\"k8s\"` (the `publish` command does this validation). Invalid provider values would fall through to the runtime's `else` branch.","time":{"start":1775857479561,"end":1775857479561}}}
